Yappod2 installation
====================

Requirements
------------

- CMake 3.20 or newer
- C and C++ compiler
- cmocka
- ICU4C
- libcurl
- libevent

Berkeley DB and zlib are not used by the v2 product.

Build and test
--------------

On macOS, Homebrew's ICU4C and curl are keg-only. Pass their Homebrew
prefixes, together with libevent, to CMake explicitly:

    brew install cmake cmocka icu4c libevent curl
    MODERN_PREFIXES="$(brew --prefix icu4c);$(brew --prefix libevent);$(brew --prefix curl)"
    cmake -S . -B build \
      -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \
      -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH="$MODERN_PREFIXES"
    cmake --build build -j
    ctest --test-dir build --output-on-failure

Use a new build directory if a previous configure cached ICU headers from the
Xcode SDK. On systems where all dependencies are in standard search paths:

    cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
    cmake --build build -j
    ctest --test-dir build --output-on-failure

Install
-------

    cmake --install build --prefix "$HOME/yappod2"

Installed executables are:

- `yappo_makeindex`: prepare canonical input, build an index, or publish updates
- `search`: run lexical, vector, or hybrid search against a v2 index
- `yappo_compact`: compact live records and collect orphan segments
- `yappod_core`: serve the internal v2 frame protocol
- `yappod_front`: serve the v2 HTTP API

See README.md for a clean-checkout indexing and search example.
